          Just to clarify a few things. It is indeed true that most often than not, big teams like Real Madrid get a few more whistles in their favor at times when playing smaller teams...especially some fouls that otherwise might not be given, are given. BUT this does not mean that every single team playing against the big teams are hurt by the referee. It does happen, but not as often as people tend to cry about. Now specifically in this game, without having proper education on the referee guidelines and rules and all that they are taught, i am of the belief that there were wrong calls for both teams. A clear goal that was cancelled for Ronaldo, a penalty that might be a bit "soft" (meaning that there is contact but is it enough to justify a penalty?), an offside for Ludogorets that may have had proven to be a goalscoring opportunity...not to mention a few cards that players of both teams could have gotten for diving. I do not believe those mistakes were intentional, but simple wrong calls.
